          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A scroller displays a slot containing a knob that the user can drag directly to the desired location. The knob indicates both the position within the document view andâ€”by varying in size within the slotâ€”the amount visible relative to the size of the document view."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Typically, you donâ€™t need to program with scrollers; instead, you configure them with an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsscrollview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object in a "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Nib file",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/DevPedia-CocoaCore/NibFile.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40008195-CH34"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Donâ€™t use an scroller when a slider would be more appropriate. An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsslider"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object represents a range of values for something in the application and lets the user choose a setting. A scroller represents the relative position of the visible portion of a view and lets the user choose which portion to view."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
